Package grafioschtrader.connector.instrument

Interface IFeedConnector

All Known Implementing Classes:
AlphaVantageFeedConnector, BaseFeedApiKeyConnector, BaseFeedConnector, BoursoramaFeedConnector, ComdirectFeedConnector, ConsorsbankFeedConnector, CryptoCompareFeedConnector, DivvyDiaryConnector, EcbCrossRateConnector, EodHistoricalDataConnector, EuronextFeedConnector, FinanzenCHFeedConnector, FinanzenConnetorBase, FinanzenNETFeedConnector, FinnhubConnector, FxUbcFeedConnector, InvestingConnector, OnvistaFeedConnector, SixFeedConnector, StockDataFeedConnector, SwissFundDataConnector, TwelvedataFeedConnector, ViennaStockExchangeFeedConnector, WarsawGpwFeedConnector, XetraFeedConnector, YahooFeedConnectorCOM
public interface IFeedConnector
Connector interface for data providers that supply financial market data.

This interface defines the contract for connectors that can retrieve various types of financial data including historical prices, intraday prices, dividends, and stock splits for both securities and currency pairs from external data sources.

Supported Data Types

  • Historical Data (FS_HISTORY): End-of-day price data over time periods
  • Intraday Data (FS_INTRA): Real-time or delayed price updates
  • Dividend Data (FS_DIVIDEND): Dividend payment information for securities
  • Split Data (FS_SPLIT): Stock split events and ratios

Data Provider Integration

Implementations should handle:

  • Authentication and API key management for premium data sources
  • Rate limiting and request throttling
  • Error handling and retry mechanisms
  • Data format parsing and validation
  • URL construction for different data types

Validation and Quality Control

Connectors provide validation capabilities including:

  • URL pattern validation using regex
  • HTTP connectivity checks
  • Data provider response validation
  • Instrument availability verification

    • getNextAttemptInDaysForSplitHistorical

      Integer getNextAttemptInDaysForSplitHistorical(Date splitDate)
      Calculates the number of days to wait before the next attempt to check if historical price data reflects a stock split. Recent splits may take several days to be reflected in adjusted historical prices from data providers.
      Parameters:
      splitDate - the date when the stock split occurred
      Returns:
      number of days to wait before next check, or null if no further checks needed

    • isDownloadLinkCreatedLazy

      EnumSet<IFeedConnector.DownloadLink> isDownloadLinkCreatedLazy()
      Returns which data provider the content of the links for the frontend must be created in the backend. Normally, the frontend receives a URL that can be opened directly in the browser. This is not possible for data providers with API keys, so the data content is prepared in the backend. There are other cases where the data content must be created in the backend.
      Returns:
      set of download link types requiring special handling

    • getContentOfPageRequest

      String getContentOfPageRequest(String httpPageUrl)
      The user interface receives a link to check the price data provider of a security. If an API key is required, only the backend can evaluate this link and return the corresponding content. The content of the provider may also be determined in the backend for other reasons.
      Parameters:
      httpPageUrl - the URL to fetch content from
      Returns:
      the content of the requested page, typically formatted for HTML display
